President Obama has announced his intent to nominate and appoint several individuals to key administration posts. Timothy Hyungrock Haahs is nominated for the Board of Directors of the National Institute of Building Sciences. Morton H. Halperin is nominated for the Board of Directors of the Millennium Challenge Corporation. David Christiani, Judy E. Garber, Liz Jaffee, Beth Karlan, Mack Roach III, and Charles Sawyers are appointed as members of the National Cancer Advisory Board. Each individual has a unique background and experience in their respective fields. President Obama is confident that they will serve ably in their roles and looks forward to working with them in the coming months and years.